ellowships  a service learning program that encourages students to take care of the most vulnerable members of society Schweitzer Fellowships Inspire Discovery  UIC scientist wins national fellowship for excellence in teaching UIC scientist Max Berkelhammer s research and teaching aims to dissolve the preconceived notion that the field of geoscience is limited to studying rocks  Berkelhammer is among the first to win the Excellence in Teaching Fellowship  which will support research and employ a graduate student to help Berkelhammer further the study of earth sciences as it relates to urban populations UIC scientist Max Berkelhammer Transform Lives      M grant aims to improve behavioral health care delivery Thanks to a generous grant from the Health Resources and Services Administration  JACSW graduate students will be receiving specialized training to help them better serve the individuals in Chicago s marginalized communities who suffer from mental health issues specialized training Cultivate Potential  Curtis Granderson hosts the  th annual  Grand Kids Academy All Star Camp  at Granderson Stadium MLB All Star and UIC alumnus Curtis Granderson returned to campus to host his Grand Kids Academy All Star Camp  which focuses on fitness  nutrition and education for children from disadvantaged areas in Chicago Curtis Granderson UIC Campus Film Office works to bring more crews to  Chicago s Most Film Friendly Campus UIC has given major motion pictures the landscape to tell stories on the big screen for the past three decades  with notable screen credits in horror movie "Child  s Play  comedy classic "The Blue Brothers  and popular TV shows like "Empire" and "Shameless  The newly formed UIC Campus Film Office is set to formalize our campus filming program and turn UIC into a one stop shop for Chicago  s growing film industry UIC Campus Film Office Looking for ways to share your important life events and accomplishments with the UIC family  Submit a class note on our webs